laboratory_examinations.findings: Left-sided slowing and attenuation, no epileptiform activity.
Decreased cerebral perfusion predominantly of the left frontoparietal cortex.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Post-embolization scan demonstrated enhanced perfusion of the left frontoparietal lobe, especially the left dorsolateral prefrontal cortex.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Confirmed the presence of a giant high flow dural arteriovenous fistula at the middle third of the superior sagittal sinus.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up angiogram at the time of embolization showed obliteration of the anomaly.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Positive for a lupus anticoagulant by the dilute Russell viper venom time assay.
